title: 【精选】【榜单】1001 Video Games
description: In 2010 (later updated in 2013) a book was published titled "1001 Video Games You Must Play Before You Die." While the list is very weird (for example, it only includes the third Donkey Kong Country game), it does a decent job at listing a lot of important and great games of all styles, and many of those either were originally developed in Flash, had a Flash (or other web) version, or were exclusively browser games. Those games are collected here.
author: Gibus Wearing Brony

games.notes: The book includes the Zynga mobile app Drop7, which has its development roots in this game that was used in a Numb3rs ARG.
The book includes the console port, N+.
The book includes the mobile port, which has improved graphics but identical gameplay.
